17bebc8f-1161-46b8-a774-6989bd0dd16f.0bff5c65-8a20-4616-b064-f457efe8bc40.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

17bebc8f-1161-46b8-a774-6989bd0dd16f.7d0f0d29-b785-4e0d-893e-d48db0ca62ec.description=Retrieves a system account username and password and stores the values as flow variables. Inputs\: accountName - The name of the system account. Starting with OO Platform version 10.20, the relative path of the system account can also be used. flowVariable - The flow variables prefix to store the system account into. The operation will receive one input with the flow variable name to assign to, but will actually assign the account to two separate variables. So if the input flowVar was "sysAcct" then two flow vars will be created "sysAcctUsername" and "sysAcctPassword". Results\: Result - A message indicating if the operation was successful or not. 17bebc8f-1161-46b8-a774-6989bd0dd16f.description=
This flow will check for attachment presence, parse attachment for new application or existing loan details and return the values in a structured list

Inputs\:
    hasAttachment- if the email has attachments. True, Flase
    emailAttachement - attachmentId of the email

Results\:
    ddrType - type of the DDR
    CustomerLastName - last name of the customer
    loanNumberC - calculated loan Number
    requestedPaymentFrequencyC - calculated payment frequency
    requestedRepaymentOptionC - calculated Repayment option
    repaymentDay - day of the repayment (Ex\: Sunday, Monday...)
    preferredStartDay - preferred start day is in date format
    additionalAmountC - calculated additional amount
    draftAmountC - calculated draft amount
    draftAccountName - name of the account
    draftBSB - Draft BSB first 6 charectors of the account number
    accountNumber - account number of the customer
    draftFinancialInstitution - name of the Bank
    readFormFailFlag - if failed to read the email then set this flag True else False
    signaturesFlag - data recieved from DDRForm values will be True or False
    branchStampFlag - data recieved from DDRForm values will be True or False
errorMessages [List] - failure Messages


Responses\:
    Success – Proceed to Standardize Email Content
    Failure – Proceed to Check For Failure Flags
